By Cecilia Ijuo Abuja –   The Senate on Thursday adjourned plenary till July 3 to proceed for Sallah break. The President of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki made the announcement shortly before adjourning plenary. The Senate had in the course of the day’s plenary, deliberated on declaration of June 12 as public holiday by President Muhammadu Buhari. The senate also confirmed Justice Adamu Abdu-Kafarati among other things. (NAN)